    align:confidence "0.95"^^xsd:float ;
    align:rationale "Both definitions refer to a computational/mathematical entity used for inference or task execution. While the AIDOC definition is slightly more general in phrasing ('enables an AI method'), the core meaning aligns perfectly with the 'inference or prediction' focus of the airo concept. The lexical similarity score of 1.0 further supports this strong alignment."^^xsd:string ;
    align:relation skos:exactMatch ;
    align:source aidoc:AIModel ;
    align:target <https://w3id.org/airo#AIModel> .

align:97732387-8444-4364-bd5e-15b1e56e01b8 a prov:Entity,
        align:Mapping ;
    prov:wasAttributedTo align:LLMAlignmentBot ;
    prov:wasGeneratedBy align:06435388-2333-4b31-b2c8-4d96c2ac67ab ;
    align:confidence "1.0"^^xsd:float ;
    align:rationale "The labels are identical and the lexical similarity score is perfect (1.0). While the AIDOC description is more verbose, it doesn't introduce any differing semantics; it simply elaborates on what a 'Dataset' *is* within the AI lifecycle. The airo concept explicitly references DCAT, a widely accepted standard for describing datasets."^^xsd:string ;
    align:relation skos:exactMatch ;
    align:source aidoc:Dataset ;
    align:target <https://www.w3.org/TR/vocab-dcat-3/Dataset> .

align:bff5bdd1-ab22-499e-9630-ab4dfcd47fc2 a prov:Entity,
        align:Mapping ;
    prov:wasAttributedTo align:LLMAlignmentBot ;
    prov:wasGeneratedBy align:06435388-2333-4b31-b2c8-4d96c2ac67ab ;
    align:confidence "0.85"^^xsd:float ;
    align:rationale "The `airo#AISystem` concept defines *what* an AI system is – a broad definition encompassing its characteristics and operation. The `AI System Capability` focuses on *what an AI system can do*, representing specific functions or tasks. Therefore, capability is a component *of* an AI system; the airo concept is broader."^^xsd:string ;
    align:relation skos:broadMatch ;
    align:source aidoc:AISystemCapability ;
    align:target <https://w3id.org/airo#AISystem> .

align:c3dfe040-35fc-414e-9670-fcbd8bb2e896 a prov:Entity,
        align:Mapping ;
    prov:wasAttributedTo align:LLMAlignmentBot ;
    prov:wasGeneratedBy align:06435388-2333-4b31-b2c8-4d96c2ac67ab ;
    align:confidence "0.85"^^xsd:float ;
    align:rationale "The `airo#Change` concept is very general – any alteration to *anything*. The `AIDOC Change Log` is a specific *type* of change - those recorded relating to a system's lifecycle. Therefore, the AIDOC concept is narrower and falls under the broader `airo#Change`."^^xsd:string ;
    align:relation skos:broadMatch ;
    align:source aidoc:ChangeLog ;
    align:target <https://w3id.org/airo#Change> .

