    align:rationale "Both concepts refer to 'Standard' and share a similar high-level definition. However, the airo concept explicitly defines standards as *not* compulsory, while the AIDOC description doesn’t make this distinction. This nuance prevents an exact match but indicates strong similarity suitable for interchangeability in many contexts."^^xsd:string ;
    align:relation skos:closeMatch ;
    align:source aidoc:Standard ;
    align:target <https://w3id.org/airo#Standard> .

